INSERT INTO `subtitle` (`id`, `number`, `content`, `episode_id`) VALUES
(1, '1', 'Easy, boy.', 1),
(2, '10', 'Our orders were to track the wildlings.', 1),
(3, '100', '- Right. Give it here. - No!', 1),
(4, '101', 'Put away your blade.', 1),
(5, '102', '- I take orders from your father, not you. - Please, Father!', 1),
(6, '103', 'I\'m sorry, Bran.', 1),
(7, '104', 'Lord Stark?', 1),
(8, '105', 'There are five pups.', 1),
(9, '106', 'One for each of the Stark children.', 1),
(10, '107', 'The direwolf is the sigil of your house.', 1),
(11, '108', 'They were meant to have them.', 1),
(12, '109', 'You will train them yourselves.', 1),
(13, '11', 'We tracked them. They won\'t trouble us no more.', 1),
(14, '110', 'You will feed them yourselves.', 1),
(15, '111', 'And if they die, you will bury them yourselves.', 1),
(16, '112', 'What about you?', 1),
(17, '113', 'I\'m not a Stark.', 1),
(18, '114', 'Get on.', 1),
(19, '115', 'What is it?', 1),
(20, '116', 'The runt of the litter. That one\'s yours, Snow.', 1),
(21, '117', 'As your brother, I feel it\'s my duty to warn you...', 1),
(22, '118', 'you worry too much.', 1),
(23, '119', '- It\'s starting to show. - And you never worry about anything.', 1),
(24, '12', 'You don\'t think he\'ll ask us how they died?', 1),
(25, '120', 'When we were seven and you jumped off the cliffs at Casterly Rock,', 1),
(26, '121', '100-foot drop into the water... you were never afraid.', 1),
(27, '122', 'There was nothing to be afraid of until you told Father.', 1),
(28, '123', '\"We\'re Lannisters. Lannisters don\'t act like fools.\"', 1),
(29, '124', '- What if Jon Arryn told someone? - But who would he tell?', 1),
(30, '125', 'My husband.', 1),
(31, '126', 'If he told the king, both our heads would be skewered on the city gates by now.', 1),
(32, '127', 'Whatever Jon Arryn knew or didn\'t know, it died with him.', 1),
(33, '128', 'And Robert will choose a new Hand of the King,', 1),
(34, '129', 'someone to do his job while he\'s off fucking boars and hunting whores.', 1),
(35, '13', 'Get back on your horse.', 1),
(36, '130', 'Or is it the other way around?', 1),
(37, '131', 'And life will go on.', 1),
(38, '132', 'You should be the Hand of the King.', 1),
(39, '133', 'That\'s an honour I can do without.', 1),
(40, '134', 'Their days are too long,', 1),
(41, '135', 'their lives are too short.', 1),
(42, '136', 'All these years,', 1),
(43, '137', 'and I still feel like an outsider when I come here.', 1),
(44, '138', 'You have five northern children.', 1),
(45, '139', 'You\'re not an outsider.', 1),
(46, '14', 'Whatever did it to them could do it to us.', 1),
(47, '140', 'I wonder if the old gods agree.', 1),
(48, '141', 'It\'s your gods with all the rules.', 1),
(49, '142', 'I am so sorry, my love.', 1),
(50, '143', '- Tell me. - There was a raven from King\'s Landing.', 1),
(51, '144', 'Jon Arryn is dead.', 1),
(52, '145', 'A fever took him.', 1),
(53, '146', 'I know he was like a father to you.', 1),
(54, '147', '- Your sister, the boy? - They both have their health,', 1),
(55, '148', 'gods be good.', 1),
(56, '149', 'The raven brought more news.', 1),
(57, '15', 'They even killed the children.', 1),
(58, '150', 'The king rides for Winterfell...', 1),
(59, '151', 'with the queen and all the rest of them.', 1),
(60, '152', 'If he\'s coming this far north...', 1),
(61, '153', 'there\'s only one thing he\'s after.', 1),
(62, '154', 'You can always say no, Ned.', 1),
(63, '155', 'We\'ll need plenty of candles for Lord Tyrion\'s chamber.', 1),
(64, '156', '- I\'m told he reads all night. - I\'m told he drinks all night.', 1),
(65, '157', 'How much could he possibly drink? A man of his...', 1),
(66, '158', 'stature?', 1),
(67, '159', 'We\'ve brought up eight barrels of ale from the cellar.', 1),
(68, '16', 'It\'s a good thing we\'re not children.', 1),
(69, '160', 'Perhaps we\'ll find out.', 1),
(70, '161', 'In any case, candles.', 1),
(71, '162', 'Why is your mother so dead set on us getting pretty for the king?', 1),
(72, '163', 'It\'s for the queen, I bet. I hear she\'s a sleek bit of mink.', 1),
(73, '164', 'I hear the prince is a right royal prick.', 1),
(74, '165', 'Think of all those southern girls he gets to stab with his right royal prick.', 1),
(75, '166', 'Go on, Tommy, shear him good.', 1),
(76, '167', 'He\'s never met a girl he likes better than his own hair.', 1),
(77, '168', 'Gods, but they grow fast.', 1),
(78, '169', 'Brandon!', 1),
(79, '17', 'You want to run away south, run away.', 1),
(80, '170', 'I saw the king. He\'s got hundreds of people.', 1),
(81, '171', 'How many times have I told you? No climbing.', 1),
(82, '172', 'But he\'s coming right now, down our road.', 1),
(83, '173', 'I want you to promise me,', 1),
(84, '174', 'no more climbing.', 1),
(85, '175', 'I promise.', 1),
(86, '176', '- Do you know what? - What?', 1),
(87, '177', 'You always look at your feet before you lie.', 1),
(88, '178', 'Run and find your father.', 1),
(89, '179', 'Tell him the king is close.', 1),
(90, '18', 'Of course, they will behead you as a deserter.', 1),
(91, '180', 'Where\'s Arya? Sansa, where\'s your sister?', 1),
(92, '181', '- Hey, hey, hey, hey. - Oh.', 1),
(93, '182', 'What are you doing with that on?', 1),
(94, '183', 'Go on.', 1),
(95, '184', 'Move!', 1),
(96, '185', 'Your Grace.', 1),
(97, '186', 'You\'ve got fat.', 1),
(98, '187', '- Cat! - Your Grace.', 1),
(99, '188', 'Nine years... Why haven\'t I seen you? Where the hell have you been?', 1),
(100, '189', 'Guarding the North for you, Your Grace. Winterfell is yours.', 1),
(101, '19', 'If I don\'t catch you first.', 1),
(102, '190', '- Where\'s the Imp? - Will you shut up?', 1),
(103, '191', 'Who have we here?', 1),
(104, '192', 'You must be Robb.', 1),
(105, '193', 'My, you\'re a pretty one.', 1),
(106, '194', 'Your name is?', 1),
(107, '195', 'Arya.', 1),
(108, '196', 'Oh, show us your muscles.', 1),
(109, '197', 'You\'ll be a soldier.', 1),
(110, '198', 'That\'s Jaime Lannister, the queen\'s twin brother.', 1),
(111, '199', 'Would you please shut up?', 1),
(112, '2', 'What do you expect? They\'re savages.', 1),
(113, '20', 'Get back on your horse.', 1),
(114, '200', 'My queen.', 1),
(115, '201', 'My queen.', 1),
(116, '202', 'Take me to your crypt. I want to pay my respects.', 1),
(117, '203', 'We\'ve been riding for a month, my love.', 1),
(118, '204', 'Surely the dead can wait.', 1),
(119, '205', 'Ned.', 1),
(120, '206', 'Where\'s the Imp?', 1),
(121, '207', 'Where is our brother?', 1),
(122, '208', 'Go and find the little beast.', 1),
(123, '209', 'Tell me about Jon Arryn.', 1),
(124, '21', 'I won\'t say it again.', 1),
(125, '210', 'One minute he was fine and then...', 1),
(126, '211', 'burned right through him, whatever it was.', 1),
(127, '212', 'I loved that man.', 1),
(128, '213', 'We both did.', 1),
(129, '214', 'He never had to teach you much, but me? You remember me at 16?', 1),
(130, '215', 'All I wanted to do', 1),
(131, '216', 'was crack skulls and fuck girls.', 1),
(132, '217', '- He showed me what was what. - Aye.', 1),
(133, '218', 'Don\'t look at me like that. It\'s not his fault I didn\'t listen.', 1),
(134, '219', 'I need you, Ned,', 1),
(135, '22', 'Your dead men seem to have moved camp.', 1),
(136, '220', 'down at King\'s Landing, not up here where you\'re no damn use to anybody.', 1),
(137, '221', 'Lord Eddard Stark...', 1),
(138, '222', 'I would name you the Hand of the King.', 1),
(139, '223', 'I\'m not worthy of the honour.', 1),
(140, '224', 'I\'m not trying to honour you.', 1),
(141, '225', 'I\'m trying to get you to run my kingdom', 1),
(142, '226', 'while I eat, drink and whore my way to an early grave.', 1),
(143, '227', 'Damn it, Ned, stand up.', 1),
(144, '228', 'You helped me win the Iron Throne,', 1),
(145, '229', 'now help me keep the damn thing.', 1),
(146, '23', 'They were here.', 1),
(147, '230', 'We were meant to rule together.', 1),
(148, '231', 'If your sister had lived, we\'d have been bound by blood.', 1),
(149, '232', 'Well, it\'s not too late.', 1),
(150, '233', 'I have a son, you have a daughter.', 1),
(151, '234', 'We\'ll join our houses.', 1),
(152, '235', 'It is true what they say about the northern girls.', 1),
(153, '236', 'Did you hear the king\'s in Winterfell?', 1),
(154, '237', 'I did hear something about that.', 1),
(155, '238', 'And the queen and her twin brother.', 1),
(156, '239', 'They say that he is the most handsome man in the Seven Kingdoms.', 1),
(157, '24', 'See where they went.', 1),
(158, '240', 'And the other brother?', 1),
(159, '241', '- The queen has two brothers? - There\'s the pretty one...', 1),
(160, '242', 'and there\'s the clever one.', 1),
(161, '243', 'Mmm...', 1),
(162, '244', 'I hear they call him the Imp.', 1),
(163, '245', 'I hear he hates that nickname.', 1),
(164, '246', 'Oh? I hear he\'s more than earned it.', 1),
(165, '247', 'I hear he\'s a drunken little lecher,', 1),
(166, '248', 'prone to all manner of perversions.', 1),
(167, '249', 'Clever girl.', 1),
(168, '25', 'What is it?', 1),
(169, '250', 'We\'ve been expecting you, Lord Tyrion.', 1),
(170, '251', 'Have you?', 1),
(171, '252', '- Already? - Oh!', 1),
(172, '253', 'The gods gave me one blessing.', 1),
(173, '254', '- Don\'t get up. - My lord.', 1),
(174, '255', 'Should I explain to you the meaning of a closed door in a whorehouse, brother?', 1),
(175, '256', 'You have much to teach me, no doubt,', 1),
(176, '257', 'but our sister craves your attention.', 1),
(177, '258', 'She has odd cravings, our sister.', 1),
(178, '259', 'A family trait.', 1),
(179, '26', 'It\'s...', 1),
(180, '260', 'Now, the Starks are feasting us at sundown.', 1),
(181, '261', '- Don\'t leave me alone with these people. - I\'m sorry, I\'ve begun the feast a bit early.', 1),
(182, '262', 'And this is the first of many courses.', 1),
(183, '263', 'I thought you might say that.', 1),
(184, '264', 'But since we\'re short on time...', 1),
(185, '265', 'Come on, girls.', 1),
(186, '266', 'See you at sundown.', 1),
(187, '267', 'Close the door!', 1),
(188, '268', 'Did you have to bury her in a place like this?', 1),
(189, '269', 'She should be on a hill somewhere', 1),
(190, '27', 'Go on, Father\'s watching.', 1),
(191, '270', 'with the sun and the clouds above her.', 1),
(192, '271', 'She was my sister.', 1),
(193, '272', 'This is where she belongs.', 1),
(194, '273', 'She belonged with me.', 1),
(195, '274', 'In my dreams, I kill him every night.', 1),
(196, '275', 'It\'s done, Your Grace. The Targaryens are gone.', 1),
(197, '276', 'Not all of them.', 1),
(198, '277', 'Daenerys!', 1),
(199, '278', 'Daenerys.', 1),
(200, '279', 'There\'s our bride-to-be.', 1),
(201, '28', 'And your mother.', 1),
(202, '280', 'Look, a gift from Illyrio.', 1),
(203, '281', 'Touch it.', 1),
(204, '282', 'Go on, feel the fabric.', 1),
(205, '283', 'Mmm.', 1),
(206, '284', 'Isn\'t he a gracious host?', 1),
(207, '285', 'We\'ve been his guests for over a year and he\'s never asked us for anything.', 1),
(208, '286', 'Illyrio\'s no fool.', 1),
(209, '287', 'He knows I won\'t forget my friends', 1),
(210, '288', 'when I come into my throne.', 1),
(211, '289', 'You still slouch.', 1),
(212, '29', 'Fine work, as always. Well done.', 1),
(213, '290', 'Let them see.', 1),
(214, '291', 'You have a woman\'s body now.', 1),
(215, '292', 'I need you to be perfect today.', 1),
(216, '293', 'Can you do that for me?', 1),
(217, '294', 'You don\'t want to wake the dragon, do you?', 1),
(218, '295', 'No.', 1),
(219, '296', 'When they write the history of my reign, sweet sister,', 1),
(220, '297', 'they will say it began today.', 1),
(221, '298', 'It\'s too hot, my lady.', 1),
(222, '299', 'Where is he?', 1),
(223, '3', 'One lot steals a goat from another lot,', 1),
(224, '30', 'Thank you.', 1),
(225, '300', 'The Dothraki are not known for their punctuality.', 1),
(226, '301', 'Athchomar chomakaan, Khal vezhven.', 1),
(227, '302', 'May I present my honoured guests?', 1),
(228, '303', 'Viserys of House Targaryen,', 1),
(229, '304', 'the third of his name,', 1),
(230, '305', 'the rightful King of the Andals and the First Men,', 1),
(231, '306', 'and his sister,', 1),
(232, '307', 'Daenerys of House Targaryen.', 1),
(233, '308', 'Do you see how long his hair is?', 1),
(234, '309', 'When Dothraki are defeated in combat', 1),
(235, '31', 'I love the detail that you\'ve managed to get in these corners.', 1),
(236, '310', 'they cut off their braid so the whole world can see their shame.', 1),
(237, '311', 'Khal Drogo has never been defeated.', 1),
(238, '312', 'He\'s a savage, of course, but he\'s one of the finest killers alive.', 1),
(239, '313', 'And you will be his queen.', 1),
(240, '314', 'Come forward, my dear.', 1),
(241, '315', 'Where is he going?', 1),
(242, '316', '- The ceremony is over. - But he... But he didn\'t say anything.', 1),
(243, '317', 'Did he like her?', 1),
(244, '318', 'Trust me, Your Grace, if he didn\'t like her, we\'d know.', 1),
(245, '319', 'It won\'t be long now.', 1),
(246, '32', 'Quite beautiful.', 1),
(247, '320', 'Soon you will cross the narrow sea and take back your father\'s throne.', 1),
(248, '321', 'The people drink secret toasts to your health.', 1),
(249, '322', 'They cry out for their true king.', 1),
(250, '323', 'When will they be married?', 1),
(251, '324', 'Soon. The Dothraki never stay still for long.', 1),
(252, '325', 'Is it true they lie with their horses?', 1),
(253, '326', 'I wouldn\'t ask Khal Drogo.', 1),
(254, '327', 'Do you take me for a fool?', 1),
(255, '328', 'I take you for a king.', 1),
(256, '329', 'Kings lack the caution of common men.', 1),
(257, '33', 'The stitching...', 1),
(258, '330', 'My apologies if I\'ve given offence.', 1),
(259, '331', 'I know how to play a man like Drogo.', 1),
(260, '332', 'I give him a queen and he gives me an army.', 1),
(261, '333', 'I don\'t want to be his queen.', 1),
(262, '334', 'I want to go home.', 1),
(263, '335', 'So do I.', 1),
(264, '336', 'I want us both to go home,', 1),
(265, '337', 'but they took it from us.', 1),
(266, '338', 'So tell me, sweet sister,', 1),
(267, '339', 'how do we go home?', 1),
(268, '34', 'Oh, no, no, no. This stitch is very...', 1),
(269, '340', 'I don\'t know.', 1),
(270, '341', 'We go home with an army.', 1),
(271, '342', 'With Khal Drogo\'s army.', 1),
(272, '343', 'I would let his whole tribe fuck you,', 1),
(273, '344', 'all 40,000 men and their horses too,', 1),
(274, '345', 'if that\'s what it took.', 1),
(275, '346', 'Do you think Joffrey will like me?', 1),
(276, '347', 'What if he thinks I\'m ugly?', 1),
(277, '348', 'Then he is the stupidest prince that ever lived.', 1),
(278, '349', 'He\'s so handsome.', 1),
(279, '35', '- It\'s beautiful. - Thank you.', 1),
(280, '350', 'When would we be married? Soon? Or do we have to wait?', 1),
(281, '351', 'Hush now. Your father hasn\'t even said yes.', 1),
(282, '352', 'Why would he say no?', 1),
(283, '353', 'He\'d be the second most powerful man in the kingdoms.', 1),
(284, '354', 'He\'d have to leave home.', 1),
(285, '355', 'He\'d have to leave me.', 1),
(286, '356', 'And so would you.', 1),
(287, '357', 'You left your home to come here.', 1),
(288, '358', 'And I\'d be queen someday.', 1),
(289, '359', 'Please make Father say yes!', 1),
(290, '36', 'And which one of you was a marksman at ten?', 1),
(291, '360', '- Sansa... - Please, please!', 1),
(292, '361', 'It\'s the only thing I ever wanted.', 1),
(293, '362', 'Fill that up! Boys, Rodrik, come on.', 1),
(294, '363', 'Come on!', 1),
(295, '364', 'Come here, you little beauty!', 1),
(296, '365', 'Is he dead yet?', 1),
(297, '366', 'Uncle Benjen.', 1),
(298, '367', 'You got bigger.', 1),
(299, '368', 'Rode all day.', 1),
(300, '369', 'Didn\'t want to leave you alone with the Lannisters.', 1),
(301, '37', 'Keep practicing, Bran.', 1),
(302, '370', 'Why aren\'t you at the feast?', 1),
(303, '371', 'Lady Stark thought it might insult the royal family', 1),
(304, '372', 'to seat a bastard in their midst.', 1),
(305, '373', 'Well, you\'re always welcome on the Wall.', 1),
(306, '374', 'No bastard was ever refused a seat there.', 1),
(307, '375', 'So take me with you when you go back.', 1),
(308, '376', '- Jon... - Father will let me if you ask him.', 1),
(309, '377', 'I know he will.', 1),
(310, '378', 'The Wall isn\'t going anywhere.', 1),
(311, '379', 'I\'m ready to swear your oath.', 1),
(312, '38', 'Go on.', 1),
(313, '380', 'You don\'t understand what you\'d be giving up.', 1),
(314, '381', 'We have no families.', 1),
(315, '382', '- None of us will ever father sons. - I don\'t care about that.', 1),
(316, '383', 'You might, if you knew what it meant.', 1),
(317, '384', 'I\'d better get inside,', 1),
(318, '385', 'rescue your father from his guests.', 1),
(319, '386', 'We\'ll talk later.', 1),
(320, '387', 'Your uncle\'s in the Night\'s Watch.', 1),
(321, '388', 'What are you doing back there?', 1),
(322, '389', 'Preparing for a night with your family.', 1),
(323, '39', 'Don\'t think too much, Bran.', 1),
(324, '390', 'I\'ve always wanted to see the Wall.', 1),
(325, '391', 'You\'re Tyrion Lannister,', 1),
(326, '392', 'the queen\'s brother?', 1),
(327, '393', 'My greatest accomplishment.', 1),
(328, '394', 'And you, you\'re Ned Stark\'s bastard, aren\'t you?', 1),
(329, '395', 'Did I offend you? Sorry.', 1),
(330, '396', 'You are the bastard, though.', 1),
(331, '397', 'Lord Eddard Stark is my father.', 1),
(332, '398', 'And Lady Stark is not your mother,', 1),
(333, '399', 'making you... the bastard.', 1),
(334, '4', 'before you know it they\'re ripping each other to pieces.', 1),
(335, '40', 'Relax your bow arm.', 1),
(336, '400', 'Let me give you some advice, bastard.', 1),
(337, '401', 'Never forget what you are.', 1),
