(5207, '534', 'We shall require 3,000 helms and shields,', 8),
(5208, '535', 'plus swords, pikes,', 8),
(5209, '536', 'gorgets, maces...', 8),
(5210, '537', 'If it please my lord, Ser Addam bids me report', 8),
(5211, '538', 'that the northmen have crossed the Neck.', 8),
(5212, '539', 'The wolf rushes into the lion\'s jaws. So be it.', 8),
(5213, '54', '- My father\'s a lord. He\'ll reward you. - She\'ll reward me - the queen!', 8),
(5214, '540', 'Kevan, command the drummers beat assembly.', 8),
(5215, '541', 'And send word to Jaime that I am moving against Robb Stark.', 8),
(5216, '542', 'At once, my lord.', 8),
(5217, '543', 'It is said that the men of the mountain clans are great warriors.', 8),
(5218, '544', 'Ride with me against my enemies', 8),
(5219, '545', 'and you shall have all my son promised you and more.', 8),
(5220, '546', 'Only if the halfman fights with us.', 8),
(5221, '547', 'Until we hold the steel he pledged us,', 8),
(5222, '548', 'the little lion\'s life is ours.', 8),
(5223, '549', 'The scouts report Lord Tywin moves north.', 8),
(5224, '55', 'Stay away!', 8),
(5225, '550', 'We need to get him on broken ground, put his knights at a disadvantage.', 8),
(5226, '551', 'No, we need to get around him and break Jaime Lannister\'s siege of Riverrun.', 8),
(5227, '552', 'Do that and the river lords will join us.', 8),
(5228, '553', 'To do either we need to cross the river and the only crossing is at the Twins.', 8),
(5229, '554', 'Lord Frey controls that bridge. Your father\'s bannerman.', 8),
(5230, '555', '\"The late Lord Frey\" my father calls him.', 8),
(5231, '556', 'At the Trident, he didn\'t appear until the battle was done.', 8),
(5232, '557', 'Some men take their oaths more seriously than others.', 8),
(5233, '558', 'Robb\'s right. We need that bridge.', 8),
(5234, '559', 'So what\'s it going to be?', 8),
(5235, '56', 'Lord Stark, you must be thirsty.', 8),
(5236, '560', 'Do we move against Jaime or Lord Tywin?', 8),
(5237, '561', 'Your pardon, my lords. We\'ve captured a Lannister scout.', 8),
(5238, '562', 'Don\'t worry, lad. He won\'t be leaving this tent with his head.', 8),
(5239, '563', '- Where did you find him? - In the brush above the encampment.', 8),
(5240, '564', 'He looked to be counting.', 8),
(5241, '565', 'How high did you get?', 8),
(5242, '566', '20,000. Maybe more.', 8),
(5243, '567', 'You don\'t have to do this yourself. Your father would understand...', 8),
(5244, '568', 'My father understands mercy, when there is room for it.', 8),
