(5246, '57', 'Varys.', 8),
(5247, '570', 'and courage.', 8),
(5248, '571', 'Let him go.', 8),
(5249, '572', 'Robb.', 8),
(5250, '573', 'Tell Lord Tywin winter is coming for him.', 8),
(5251, '574', '20,000 northerners marching south to find out if he really does shit gold.', 8),
(5252, '575', 'Yes, my lord.', 8),
(5253, '576', 'Thank you, my lord.', 8),
(5254, '577', 'Are you touched, boy?! Letting him go?', 8),
(5255, '578', 'You call me boy again.', 8),
(5256, '579', 'Go on.', 8),
(5257, '58', 'I promise you it isn\'t poisoned.', 8),
(5258, '580', 'Oi.', 8),
(5259, '581', 'It is also the wish of His Grace', 8),
(5260, '582', 'that his loyal servant Janos Slynt,', 8),
(5261, '583', '- Commander of the City Watch... - Ser Aron.', 8),
(5262, '584', '...be at once raised to the rank of lord...', 8),
(5263, '585', 'Lord Gyles.', 8),
(5264, '586', '...and granted the ancient seat of Harrenhal,', 8),
(5265, '587', 'and that his sons and grandsons shall hold this honour', 8),
(5266, '588', 'after him until the end of time.', 8),
(5267, '589', 'In the place of the traitor Eddard Stark,', 8),
(5268, '59', 'Why is it no one ever trusts the eunuch?', 8),
(5269, '590', 'it is the wish of His Grace that Tywin Lannister,', 8),
(5270, '591', 'Lord of Casterly Rock and Warden of the West,', 8),
(5271, '592', 'be appointed Hand of the King.', 8),
(5272, '593', 'Lastly,', 8),
(5273, '594', 'in these times of treason and turmoil,', 8),
(5274, '595', 'it is the view of council', 8),
(5275, '596', 'that the life and safety', 8),
(5276, '597', 'of King Joffrey', 8),
(5277, '598', 'be of paramount importance.', 8),
(5278, '599', 'Ser Barristan Selmy.', 8),
(5279, '6', '- How she could forget... - She didn\'t forget.', 8),
(5280, '60', 'Not so much, my lord.', 8),
(5281, '600', 'Your Grace, I am yours to command.', 8),
(5282, '601', 'Rise, Ser Barristan.', 8),
(5283, '602', 'You may remove your helm.', 8),
(5284, '603', 'You have served the realm long and faithfully.', 8),
(5285, '604', 'Every man and woman in the Seven Kingdoms owes you thanks.', 8),
(5286, '605', 'But it is time to put aside your armour and your sword.', 8),
(5287, '606', 'It is time to rest and look back with pride', 8),
(5288, '607', 'on your many years of service.', 8),
(5289, '608', 'Your Grace, the Kingsguard is a sworn brotherhood.', 8),
(5290, '609', 'Our vows are taken for life. Only death relieves us of our sacred trust.', 8),
(5291, '61', 'I would save the rest, if I were you.', 8),
(5292, '610', 'Whose death, Ser Barristan? Yours or your king\'s?', 8),
(5293, '611', 'You let my father die.', 8),
(5294, '612', 'You\'re too old to protect anybody.', 8),
(5295, '613', '- Your Grace... - The council has determined', 8),
(5296, '614', 'that Ser Jaime Lannister will take your place', 8),
(5297, '615', '- as Lord Commander of the Kingsguard. - The man who profaned his blade', 8),
(5298, '616', 'with the blood of the king he had sworn to defend!', 8),
(5299, '617', 'Careful, ser.', 8),
(5300, '618', 'We have nothing but gratitude for your long service, good ser.', 8),
(5301, '619', 'You shall be given a stout keep beside the sea,', 8),
(5302, '62', 'Hide it. Men have been known to die of thirst in these cells.', 8),
(5303, '620', 'with servants to look after your every need.', 8),
(5304, '621', 'A hall to die in and men to bury me.', 8),
(5305, '622', 'I am a knight.', 8),
(5306, '623', 'I shall die a knight.', 8),
(5307, '624', 'A naked knight, apparently.', 8),
(5308, '625', 'Even now I could cut through the five of you like carving a cake!', 8),
(5309, '626', 'Here, boy!', 8),
(5310, '627', 'Melt it down and add it to the others.', 8),
(5311, '628', 'If any man in this hall has other matters', 8),
(5312, '629', 'to set before His Grace, let him speak now', 8),
(5313, '63', 'What about my daughters?', 8),
(5314, '630', 'or go forth and hold his silence.', 8),
(5315, '631', 'Your Grace.', 8),
(5316, '632', 'Come forward, my lady.', 8),
(5317, '633', 'The Lady Sansa of House Stark.', 8),
(5318, '634', 'Do you have some business for the king and the council, Sansa?', 8),
(5319, '635', 'I do.', 8),
(5320, '636', 'As it please Your Grace, I ask mercy for my father,', 8),
(5321, '637', 'Lord Eddard Stark, who was Hand of the King.', 8),
(5322, '638', 'Treason is a noxious weed.', 8),
(5323, '639', '- It should be torn out, root... - Let her speak.', 8),
(5324, '64', 'The younger one seems to have escaped the castle.', 8),
(5325, '640', 'I want to hear what she says.', 8),
(5326, '641', 'Thank you, Your Grace.', 8),
(5327, '642', 'Do you deny your father\'s crime?', 8),
(5328, '643', 'No, my lords. I know he must be punished.', 8),
(5329, '644', 'All I ask is mercy.', 8),
(5330, '645', 'I know my lord father must regret what he did.', 8),
(5331, '646', 'He was King Robert\'s friend and he loved him.', 8),
(5332, '647', 'You all know he loved him.', 8),
(5333, '648', 'He never wanted to be Hand until the king asked him.', 8),
(5334, '649', 'They must have lied to him - Lord Renly or Lord Stannis or somebody.', 8),
(5335, '65', 'Even my little birds cannot find her.', 8),
(5336, '650', 'They must have lied!', 8),
(5337, '651', 'He said I wasn\'t the king.', 8),
(5338, '652', '- Why did he say that? - He was badly hurt.', 8),
(5339, '653', 'Maester Pycelle was giving him milk of the poppy.', 8),
(5340, '654', 'He wasn\'t himself. Otherwise he never would have said it.', 8),
(5341, '655', 'A child\'s faith.', 8),
(5342, '656', 'Such sweet innocence.', 8),
(5343, '657', 'And yet they say wisdom oft comes from the mouths of babes.', 8),
(5344, '658', 'Treason is treason!', 8),
(5345, '659', 'Anything else?', 8),
(5346, '66', '- And Sansa? - Still engaged to Joffrey.', 8),
(5347, '660', 'If you still have any affection in your heart for me,', 8),
(5348, '661', 'please do me this kindness, Your Grace.', 8),
(5349, '662', 'Your sweet words have moved me.', 8),
(5350, '663', 'But your father has to confess.', 8),
(5351, '664', 'He has to confess and say that I\'m the king...', 8),
(5352, '665', 'or there\'ll be no mercy for him.', 8),
(5353, '666', 'He will.', 8),
(5354, '67', 'Cersei will keep her close. The rest of your household though...', 8),
(5355, '68', 'all dead, it grieves me to say. I do so hate the sight of blood.', 8),
(5356, '69', 'You watched my men being slaughtered and did nothing.', 8),
(5357, '7', 'She\'s with her dancing master. She\'s with him every morning.', 8),
(5358, '70', 'And would again, my lord.', 8),
(5359, '71', 'I was unarmed, unarmoured and surrounded by Lannister swords.', 8),
(5360, '72', 'When you look at me do you see a hero?', 8),
(5361, '73', 'What madness led you to tell the queen', 8),
(5362, '74', 'you had learned the truth about Joffrey\'s birth?', 8),
(5363, '75', 'The madness of mercy.', 8),
(5364, '76', '- That she might save her children. - Ah, the children.', 8),
(5365, '77', 'It\'s always the innocents who suffer.', 8),
(5366, '78', 'It wasn\'t the wine that killed Robert, nor the boar.', 8),
(5367, '79', 'The wine slowed him down and the boar ripped him open,', 8),
(5368, '8', 'She always comes back with scrapes and bruises. She\'s so clumsy.', 8),
(5369, '80', 'but it was your mercy that killed the king.', 8),
(5370, '81', 'I trust you know you\'re a dead man, Lord Eddard?', 8),
(5371, '82', 'The queen can\'t kill me. Cat holds her brother.', 8),
(5372, '83', 'The wrong brother, sadly. And lost to her.', 8),
(5373, '84', 'Your wife has let the Imp slip through her fingers.', 8),
(5374, '85', 'If that\'s true,', 8),
(5375, '86', 'then slit my throat and be done with it.', 8),
(5376, '87', 'Not today, my lord.', 8),
(5377, '88', 'Tell me something, Varys.', 8),
(5378, '89', 'Who do you truly serve?', 8),
(5379, '9', 'Hush!', 8),
(5380, '90', 'The realm, my lord.', 8),
(5381, '91', 'Someone must.', 8),
(5382, '92', 'It\'s Othor, without a doubt.', 8),
(5383, '93', 'The other one is Jafer Flowers, my lord, less the hand the wolf tore off.', 8),
(5384, '94', 'Any sign of Benjen or the rest of his party?', 8),
(5385, '95', 'Just these two, my lord. Been dead awhile, I\'d say.', 8),
(5386, '96', '- Mmm. - The smell.', 8),
(5387, '97', 'What smell?', 8),
(5388, '98', 'There is none.', 8),
(5389, '99', 'If they\'d been dead for a long time, wouldn\'t there be rot?', 8),
(5390, '1', 'You\'ve seen better days, my lord.', 9),
(5391, '10', 'I\'ve given up trying to guess.', 9),
