(5405, '112', 'The fine Lord Tully would never marry any of his children to mine.', 9),
(5406, '113', '- I\'m sure there were reasons... - I didn\'t need reasons.', 9),
(5407, '114', 'I needed to get rid of sons and daughters. You see how they pile up?', 9),
(5408, '115', 'Why are you here?', 9),
(5409, '116', 'To ask you...', 9),
(5410, '117', 'to open your gates, my lord...', 9),
(5411, '118', 'so my son and his bannermen may cross the Trident and be on their way.', 9),
(5412, '119', '- Why should I let him? - If you could climb your own battlements,', 9),
(5413, '12', 'before they cut my balls off with a hot knife -', 9),
(5414, '120', 'you would see that he has 20,000 men outside your walls.', 9),
(5415, '121', 'They\'ll be 20,000 corpses when Tywin Lannister gets here.', 9),
(5416, '122', 'Don\'t try and frighten me, Lady Stark.', 9),
(5417, '123', 'Your husband\'s in a cell beneath the Red Keep', 9),
(5418, '124', 'and your son\'s got no fur to keep his balls warm.', 9),
(5419, '125', 'You swore an oath to my father.', 9),
(5420, '126', 'Oh, yes, I said some words.', 9),
(5421, '127', 'And I swore oaths to the crown too, if I remember right.', 9),
(5422, '128', 'Joffrey\'s king now,', 9),
(5423, '129', 'which makes your boy and his corpses-to-be nothing but rebels, it seems to me.', 9),
(5424, '13', 'I travelled with a group of actors through the free cities.', 9),
(5425, '130', 'If I had the sense the gods gave a fish, I\'d hand you both over to the Lannisters.', 9),
(5426, '131', '- Why don\'t you? - Stark, Tully, Lannister, Baratheon.', 9),
(5427, '132', 'Give me one good reason why I should waste a single thought on any of you?', 9),
(5428, '133', 'And... engage!', 9),
(5429, '134', 'When does Aemon think you\'ll be able to use that hand?', 9),
(5430, '135', '- Soon, he says. - Good.', 9),
(5431, '136', 'You\'ll be ready for this, then.', 9),
(5432, '137', 'I thought a wolf was more appropriate for you than a bear...', 9),
(5433, '138', 'so I had a new pommel made. It\'s called Longclaw.', 9),
(5434, '139', 'Works as well for a wolf as a bear, I think.', 9),
(5435, '14', 'They taught me that each man has a role to play.', 9),
(5436, '140', 'This is Valyrian steel.', 9),
(5437, '141', 'It was my father\'s sword, his father before him.', 9),
(5438, '142', 'The Mormonts have carried it for five centuries.', 9),
(5439, '143', 'It was meant for my son Jorah.', 9),
(5440, '144', 'He brought dishonour to our House, but he had the grace to leave the sword', 9),
(5441, '145', 'before he fled from Westeros.', 9),
(5442, '146', '- My lord, you honour me, but I can\'t... - Oh, you can.', 9),
(5443, '147', 'And you will.', 9),
(5444, '148', 'I wouldn\'t be standing here if it wasn\'t for you and your beast.', 9),
(5445, '149', 'A bloody dead man tried to kill me.', 9),
(5446, '15', 'The same is true at court.', 9),
(5447, '150', 'So you\'ll take it. I\'ll hear no more about it.', 9),
(5448, '151', '- Is that understood? - Yes, my lord.', 9),
