(5450, '153', 'Now, don\'t think this means I approve of this nonsense with you and Alliser Thorne.', 9),
(5451, '154', 'That\'s a man\'s sword. It\'ll take a man to wield it.', 9),
(5452, '155', 'I\'ll apologise to Ser Alliser tonight.', 9),
(5453, '156', 'No, you won\'t. I sent him to King\'s Landing yesterday.', 9),
(5454, '157', 'The hand that your wolf tore off that thing\'s wrist...', 9),
(5455, '158', 'I\'ve, uh, ordered Thorne to lay it at the feet of this...', 9),
