(5498, '197', '- His men are yours, as well. -  Huh.', 9),
(5499, '198', 'Less the 400 he will keep here to hold the crossing against any who would pursue you.', 9),
(5500, '199', 'What does he want in return?', 9),
(5501, '2', 'Another visit?', 9),
(5502, '20', 'I could.', 9),
(5503, '200', 'You will be taking on his son Olyvar as your personal squire.', 9),
(5504, '201', '- He expects a knighthood in good time. - Fine, fine.', 9),
(5505, '202', 'And?', 9),
(5506, '203', 'And Arya...', 9),
(5507, '204', 'will marry his son Waldron when they both come of age.', 9),
(5508, '205', '- She won\'t be happy about that. - Hm.', 9),
(5509, '206', 'And?', 9),
(5510, '207', 'And...', 9),
(5511, '208', 'when the fighting is done...', 9),
(5512, '209', 'you will marry one of his daughters.', 9),
(5513, '21', 'But will I?', 9),
(5514, '210', 'Whichever you prefer.', 9),
(5515, '211', 'He has a number he thinks will be... suitable.', 9),
(5516, '212', 'I see.', 9),
(5517, '213', 'Did you get a look at his daughters?', 9),
(5518, '214', 'I did.', 9),
(5519, '215', 'And?', 9),
(5520, '216', 'One was...', 9),
(5521, '217', 'Do you consent?', 9),
(5522, '218', '- Can I refuse? - Not if you want to cross.', 9),
(5523, '219', 'Then I consent.', 9),
(5524, '22', 'No.', 9),
(5525, '220', 'Sam said you wanted to see me?', 9),
(5526, '221', 'I did indeed.', 9),
(5527, '222', 'Perhaps you would be kind enough to assist me.', 9),
(5528, '223', 'Tell me, did you ever wonder why the men of the Night\'s Watch', 9),
(5529, '224', 'take no wives and father no children?', 9),
(5530, '225', 'No.', 9),
(5531, '226', 'So they will not love.', 9),
(5532, '227', 'Love is the death of duty.', 9),
(5533, '228', 'If the day should ever come when your lord father was forced to choose...', 9),
(5534, '229', 'between honour on the one hand...', 9),
(5535, '23', 'As I said, I\'m no hero.', 9),
(5536, '230', 'and those he loves on the other,', 9),
(5537, '231', 'what would he do?', 9),
(5538, '232', 'He... He would do whatever was right. No matter what.', 9),
(5539, '233', 'Then Lord Stark is one man in 10,000.', 9),
(5540, '234', 'Most of us are not so strong.', 9),
(5541, '235', 'What is honour...', 9),
(5542, '236', 'compared to a woman\'s love?', 9),
(5543, '237', 'And what is duty...', 9),
(5544, '238', 'against the feel of a newborn son in your arms?', 9),
(5545, '239', 'Or a brother\'s smile?', 9),
(5546, '24', 'What do you want? Tell me.', 9),
