(10796, '665', 'All wildlings are liars and savages with no loyalty to anything or anyone.', 16),
(10797, '666', 'I done what I had to do to stay alive.', 16),
(10798, '667', 'I hate the Starks as well as you do.', 16),
(10799, '668', 'Let me serve you, my lord.', 16),
(10800, '669', 'How? And don\'t tell me to put a spear in your hand.', 16),
(10801, '67', 'Get up.', 16),
(10802, '670', 'There are other ways to serve, my lord.', 16),
(10803, '671', '- I\'m a prince now, and you\'d do well... - There are other ways to serve, my prince.', 16),
(10804, '672', 'Like what?', 16),
(10805, '673', 'We know things, the free people.', 16),
(10806, '674', 'You know things?', 16),
(10807, '675', 'Like what?', 16),
(10808, '676', 'How to eat dirt?', 16),
(10809, '677', 'Other things.', 16),
(10810, '678', 'Savage things.', 16),
(10811, '679', 'Wait outside.', 16),
(10812, '68', 'Step aside.', 16),
(10813, '680', 'I always wondered what you had under there.', 16),
(10814, '681', 'It comes at a price.', 16),
(10815, '682', 'I\'m not killing you. That\'s your price.', 16),
(10816, '683', 'I already had that.', 16),
(10817, '684', 'What do you want then,', 16),
(10818, '685', 'other than your miserable life?', 16),
(10819, '686', 'What all free people want.', 16),
(10820, '687', 'My freedom.', 16),
(10821, '688', 'Well, you shall have it, then.', 16),
(10822, '689', 'But only if you serve me well.', 16),
(10823, '69', 'Why?', 16),
(10824, '690', '- Ow! - Shh.', 16),
(10825, '691', '- It\'s not deep. - I thought they were going to kill me.', 16),
(10826, '692', 'They thought so, too.', 16),
(10827, '693', 'He hated me, the man who hit me.', 16),
(10828, '694', 'I saw it in his eyes. Hated me.', 16),
(10829, '695', 'He never met me before, but he wanted to hurt me.', 16),
(10830, '696', '- Of course he did. - Why? Why would a stranger...', 16),
(10831, '697', 'You are everything he will never have.', 16),
(10832, '698', 'Your horse eats better than his children.', 16),
(10833, '699', 'It doesn\'t matter now. He\'s dead.', 16),
(10834, '7', '- Why? - To take the castle.', 16),
(10835, '70', 'It\'s your dream, little lord.', 16),
(10836, '700', 'I would have given them bread if I had it.', 16),
(10837, '701', 'I hate the king more than any of them.', 16),
(10838, '702', 'Don\'t say these things.', 16),
(10839, '703', 'If the wrong people hear you...', 16),
(10840, '704', 'But you\'re not the wrong people.', 16),
(10841, '705', 'Don\'t trust anybody.', 16),
(10842, '706', 'Life is safer that way.', 16),
(10843, '707', 'And where are you going?', 16),
(10844, '708', 'I have something for you from Prince Theon.', 16),
(10845, '709', '- What? - Me.', 16),
(10846, '71', 'The ocean has come to swallow this place.', 16),
(10847, '710', 'He says I\'m to make the rounds.', 16),
(10848, '711', 'And keep you warm.', 16),
(10849, '712', 'The Spice King refuses me because I\'m a bad investment.', 16),
(10850, '713', 'The Silk King won\'t support me because of his business with the Lannisters.', 16),
(10851, '714', 'Why offend his best customer?', 16),
(10852, '715', 'And the Copper King offers me a single ship', 16),
(10853, '716', 'on the condition that I lie with him for a night.', 16),
(10854, '717', 'Does he think I will whore myself for a boat?', 16),
(10855, '718', 'When I came to this city, I had nothing.', 16),
(10856, '719', 'Truly nothing.', 16),
(10857, '72', 'I ain\'t letting it drown me.', 16),
(10858, '720', 'I slept by the docks.', 16),
(10859, '721', 'And when I could find work loading the ships, I would eat.', 16),
(10860, '722', 'If not, I dreamed of food.', 16),
(10861, '723', 'Today, I am the richest man in Qarth.', 16),
(10862, '724', 'Do you think the path from poverty to wealth is always pure and honourable?', 16),
(10863, '725', 'I have done many things, Khaleesi, that a righteous man would condemn.', 16),
(10864, '726', 'And here I am, with no regrets.', 16),
(10865, '727', 'Bar the gates. Ring the bells.', 16),
(10866, '728', 'Slowly, Khaleesi.', 16),
(10867, '729', 'Where are they?', 16),
(10868, '73', 'You\'ll all go about your tasks as usual.', 16),
(10869, '730', 'Where are my dragons?', 16),
(10870, '74', '- And in a few days\' time... - Greyjoy!', 16),
(10871, '75', 'We caught this one on his way back from Torrhen\'s Square.', 16),
(10872, '76', 'Took out two of ours before I got his sword.', 16),
(10873, '77', 'Ser Rodrik, it grieves me that we meet as foes.', 16),
(10874, '78', 'It grieves me you\'ve less honour than a back alley whore.', 16),
(10875, '79', 'You were raised here under this roof.', 16),
(10876, '8', '- You went with Robb. - And he sent me back to Pyke.', 16),
(10877, '80', '- These people are your people. - They are not my people.', 16),
(10878, '81', 'King Robb thought of you as a brother.', 16),
(10879, '82', 'My brothers are dead.', 16),
(10880, '83', 'They died fighting Stark men, men like you.', 16),
(10881, '84', 'Aye, they died fighting a war your father started.', 16),
(10882, '85', 'Lord Stark raised you among his own sons.', 16),
(10883, '86', 'Among them, but not one of them.', 16),
(10884, '87', 'I was his hostage, taken from my home.', 16),
(10885, '88', 'If he were alive to see this...', 16),
(10886, '89', 'He\'s not. He\'s dead.', 16),
(10887, '9', 'I\'m a Greyjoy. I can\'t fight for Robb and my father both.', 16),
(10888, '90', 'The Seven Kingdoms are at war.', 16),
(10889, '91', 'And Winterfell is mine.', 16),
(10890, '92', 'I should have put a sword in your belly instead of in your hand.', 16),
(10891, '93', 'You\'ve served this house faithfully, old man.', 16),
(10892, '94', 'But keep talking and I\'ll...', 16),
(10893, '95', 'Take him to the cells. Lock him up...', 16),
(10894, '96', 'My prince.', 16);
