(10895, '97', 'You cannot let that stand. He must pay.', 16),
(10896, '98', 'I\'ll lock him in a cell until he rots.', 16),
(10897, '99', 'No, he has to pay the iron price.', 16),
(10898, '1', 'A cripple?', 17),
(10899, '10', 'Gone, along with the wildling woman.', 17),
(10900, '100', 'So why are you fighting us?', 17),
(10901, '101', 'Go on.', 17),
(10902, '102', 'Now I want you to tell me what happened.', 17),
(10903, '103', 'Come on, this way.', 17),
(10904, '104', 'Come on, speak up. Speak up.', 17),
(10905, '105', 'Wolfsbane.', 17),
(10906, '106', 'A rare substance.', 17),
(10907, '107', 'This is no common assassin.', 17),
(10908, '108', 'We hanged 20 men last night.', 17),
(10909, '109', 'I don\'t care if you hanged 100.', 17),
(10910, '11', 'The one you were fucking.', 17),
(10911, '110', 'A man tried to kill me. I want his name and I want his head.', 17),
(10912, '111', 'We think it was an infiltrator from the Brotherhood Without Banners.', 17),
(10913, '112', 'Pretentious name for a band of outlaws.', 17),
(10914, '113', 'We can\'t allow rebels behind our lines to harass us with impunity.', 17),
(10915, '114', 'We look like fools and they look like heroes. That\'s how kings fall.', 17),
(10916, '115', 'I want them dead, every one.', 17),
(10917, '116', 'Killing them isn\'t the problem.', 17),
(10918, '117', 'It\'s finding them.', 17),
(10919, '118', 'Have you gone soft, Clegane?', 17),
(10920, '119', 'I always thought you had a talent for violence.', 17),
(10921, '12', 'Right.', 17),
(10922, '120', 'Burn the villages, burn the farms.', 17),
(10923, '121', 'Let them know what it means to choose the wrong side.', 17),
(10924, '122', 'Mmm.', 17),
(10925, '123', 'Is that mutton?', 17),
(10926, '124', 'Yes, my lord.', 17),
(10927, '125', 'Don\'t like mutton.', 17),
(10928, '126', '- I\'ll bring something else. - Leave it.', 17),
(10929, '127', '- Are you hungry? - No.', 17),
(10930, '128', 'Of course you are.', 17),
(10931, '129', 'Eat.', 17),
(10932, '13', 'Get the horses and the hounds.', 17),
(10933, '130', 'I\'ll eat in the kitchen later.', 17),
(10934, '131', 'It\'s bad manners to refuse a lord\'s offer.', 17),
(10935, '132', 'Sit.', 17),
(10936, '133', 'Eat.', 17),
(10937, '134', 'You\'re small for your age.', 17),
(10938, '135', 'I suppose you\'ve been underfed your whole life.', 17),
(10939, '136', 'I eat a lot.', 17),
(10940, '137', 'I just don\'t grow.', 17),
(10941, '138', 'Mmm.', 17),
(10942, '139', 'This will be my last war.', 17),
(10943, '14', 'Come on, find the scent.', 17),
(10944, '140', 'Win or lose.', 17),
(10945, '141', 'Have you ever lost before?', 17),
(10946, '142', 'Do you think I\'d be in my position if I had lost a war?', 17),
(10947, '143', 'But this is the one I\'ll be remembered for.', 17),
(10948, '144', 'The War of Five Kings, they\'re calling it.', 17),
(10949, '145', 'My legacy will be determined in the coming months.', 17),
(10950, '146', 'Do you know what legacy means?', 17),
(10951, '147', 'It\'s what you pass down to your children and your children\'s children.', 17),
(10952, '148', 'It\'s what remains of you when you\'re gone.', 17),
(10953, '149', 'Harren the Black thought this castle would be his legacy.', 17),
(10954, '15', 'Where they going?', 17),
(10955, '150', 'The greatest fortress ever built.', 17),
(10956, '151', 'The tallest towers, the strongest walls.', 17),
(10957, '152', 'The Great Hall had 35 hearths.', 17),
(10958, '153', 'Thirty-five. Can you imagine?', 17),
(10959, '154', 'Look at it now.', 17),
(10960, '155', 'A blasted ruin.', 17),
(10961, '156', 'Do you know what happened?', 17),
(10962, '157', 'Dragons?', 17),
(10963, '158', 'Yes.', 17),
(10964, '159', 'Dragons happened.', 17),
(10965, '16', 'Halt!', 17),
(10966, '160', 'Harrenhal was built to withstand an attack from the land.', 17),
(10967, '161', 'A million men could have marched on these walls,', 17),
(10968, '162', 'and a million men would have been repelled.', 17),
(10969, '163', 'But an attack from the air with dragon fire... Mmm-mmm.', 17),
(10970, '164', 'Harren and all his sons roasted alive within these walls.', 17),
(10971, '165', 'Aegon Targaryen changed the rules.', 17),
(10972, '166', 'That\'s why every child alive still knows his name', 17),
(10973, '167', '300 years after his death.', 17),
(10974, '168', 'Aegon and his sisters.', 17),
(10975, '169', 'Mmm?', 17),
(10976, '17', 'Enjoying your first hunt?', 17),
(10977, '170', 'It wasn\'t just Aegon riding his dragon.', 17),
(10978, '171', 'It was Rhaenys and Visenya, too.', 17),
(10979, '172', 'Correct.', 17),
(10980, '173', 'A student of history, are you?', 17),
(10981, '174', 'Rhaenys rode Meraxes.', 17),
(10982, '175', 'Visenya rode Vhagar.', 17),
(10983, '176', 'I\'m sure I knew that when I was a boy.', 17),
(10984, '177', 'Visenya Targaryen was a great warrior.', 17),
(10985, '178', 'She had a Valyrian steel sword she called Dark Sister.', 17),
(10986, '179', 'Hmm.', 17),
(10987, '18', 'So far, hunting seems very similar to riding, my lord.', 17),
(10988, '180', 'She\'s a heroine of yours, I take it?', 17),
(10989, '181', 'Aren\'t most girls more interested in the pretty maidens from the songs?', 17),
(10990, '182', 'Jonquil with the flowers in her hair?', 17),
(10991, '183', 'Most girls are idiots.', 17),
(10992, '184', 'You remind me of my daughter.', 17),
(10993, '185', 'Where did you learn all this stuff about Visenya and her Valyrian steel sword?', 17),
(10994, '186', 'From my father.', 17),
(10995, '187', 'He was a well-read stonemason.', 17),
(10996, '188', 'Can\'t say I\'ve ever met a literate stonemason.', 17),
(10997, '189', 'Have you met many stonemasons, my lord?', 17),
(10998, '19', 'With hunting, there\'s blood at the end.', 17),
(10999, '190', 'Careful now, girl.', 17),
(11000, '191', 'I enjoy you, but be careful.', 17),
(11001, '192', 'Take that back to the kitchen.', 17),
(11002, '193', 'Eat what you want.', 17),
(11003, '194', 'And, girl.', 17),
(11004, '195', '\"M\'lord.\"', 17),
(11005, '196', 'Lowborn girls say \"m\'lord,\"', 17),
(11006, '197', 'not \"my lord.\"', 17),
(11007, '198', 'If you\'re going to pose as a commoner, you should do it properly.', 17),
(11008, '199', 'My mother served Lady Dustin for many years, my lord.', 17),
(11009, '2', 'You let a cripple escape?', 17),
(11010, '20', 'They\'re little boys.', 17),
(11011, '200', 'She taught me how to speak proper... Properly.', 17),
(11012, '201', 'You\'re too smart for your own good. Has anyone told you that?', 17),
(11013, '202', 'Yes.', 17),
(11014, '203', 'Go on.', 17),
(11015, '204', 'I beg pardon, ser.', 17),
(11016, '205', 'I should have come to you after to thank you for saving me.', 17),
(11017, '206', '- You were so brave. - Brave?', 17),
(11018, '207', 'A dog doesn\'t need courage to chase off rats.', 17),
(11019, '208', 'Does it give you joy to scare people?', 17),
(11020, '209', 'No, it gives me joy to kill people.', 17),
(11021, '21', 'I was a little boy when I was torn away from my home and brought here.', 17),
(11022, '210', 'Spare me. You can\'t tell me', 17),
(11023, '211', 'Lord Eddard Stark of Winterfell never killed a man.', 17),
(11024, '212', 'It was his duty. He never liked it.', 17),
(11025, '213', 'Is that what he told you?', 17),
(11026, '214', 'He lied.', 17),
(11027, '215', 'Killing is the sweetest thing there is.', 17),
(11028, '216', 'Why are you always so hateful?', 17),
(11029, '217', 'You\'ll be glad of the hateful things I do someday when you\'re queen', 17),
(11030, '218', 'and I\'m all that stands between you and your beloved king.', 17),
(11031, '219', 'I\'ve demanded a meeting of the Thirteen. One of them did this or knows who did.', 17),
(11032, '22', 'So I kept my word. I never ran away.', 17),
(11033, '220', 'You are one of the Thirteen.', 17),
(11034, '221', 'If I wanted your dragons, I would have taken them.', 17),
(11035, '222', '- They mean nothing to me on their own. - Nothing?', 17),
(11036, '223', 'They\'re more valuable than anything in the world.', 17),
(11037, '224', 'Shall we look inside my vault', 17),
(11038, '225', 'and see what selling your dragons would buy me I cannot buy already?', 17),
(11039, '226', 'We will get them back.', 17),
(11040, '227', 'There is no we, so why would you help me get them back?', 17),
(11041, '228', 'I took you under my protection in front of the rulers of my city.', 17),
(11042, '229', 'A man is what others say he is and no more.', 17),
(11043, '23', 'If I find them soon enough, I won\'t hurt them.', 17),
(11044, '230', 'If they say that Xaro Xhoan Daxos is a liar, my word is worth nothing.', 17),
(11045, '231', 'I cannot let this thing happen to you under my roof.', 17),
(11046, '232', 'But it did happen under your roof.', 17),
(11047, '233', 'Khaleesi, many times in my life, I have been...', 17),
(11048, '234', 'I don\'t care where you\'ve been.', 17),
(11049, '235', 'You think we\'re savages because we don\'t live in stone castles.', 17),
(11050, '236', 'We can\'t make steel as good as yours, it\'s true, but...', 17),
(11051, '237', 'We\'re free.', 17),
(11052, '238', 'If someone tried to tell us we couldn\'t lie down as man and woman,', 17),
(11053, '239', 'we\'d shove a spear up his arse.', 17),
(11054, '24', 'Well, I\'ll hurt them, but I won\'t kill them.', 17),
(11055, '240', 'We don\'t go serving some shit king who\'s only king because his father was.', 17),
(11056, '241', 'No.', 17),
(11057, '242', 'No, you serve Mance Rayder, the King beyond the Wall.', 17),
(11058, '243', 'We chose Mance Rayder to lead us.', 17),
(11059, '244', 'He was a crow, same as you, but he wanted to be free.', 17),
(11060, '245', 'You could be free, too.', 17),
(11061, '246', 'You don\'t need to live your whole life taking commands from old men.', 17),
(11062, '247', 'Wake up when you want to wake up.', 17),
(11063, '248', 'I could show you the streams to fish, the woods to hunt.', 17),
(11064, '249', 'Build yourself a cabin and find a woman to lie with in the night.', 17),
(11065, '25', 'Those boys are of far more value to you alive than dead.', 17),
(11066, '250', 'You\'re a pretty lad.', 17),
(11067, '251', 'The girls would claw each other\'s eyes out to get naked with you.', 17),
(11068, '252', 'Walk.', 17),
(11069, '253', 'I could teach you how to do it.', 17),
(11070, '254', 'I know how to do it.', 17),
(11071, '255', 'You know nothing, Jon Snow.', 17),
(11072, '256', 'And what did she say?', 17),
(11073, '257', 'She admired your spirit, Your Grace.', 17),
(11074, '258', 'And what then?', 17),
(11075, '259', 'She...', 17),
(11076, '26', 'They have no value to me missing.', 17),
(11077, '260', 'If every man were held accountable for the actions of every distant relative, Ser Alton,', 17),
(11078, '261', 'we\'d all hang.', 17),
(11079, '262', 'She tore the paper in half, Your Grace.', 17),
(11080, '263', 'You\'ve acted with honour.', 17),
(11081, '264', 'I thank you for it.', 17),
(11082, '265', 'Lord Karstark, see that Ser Alton\'s pen is clean, and give him a hot supper.', 17),
(11083, '266', 'Ser Alton\'s pen is occupied, Your Grace.', 17),
(11084, '267', 'The prisoners from the Yellow Fork.', 17),
(11085, '268', 'Too many prisoners.', 17),
(11086, '269', 'Is there room for Ser Alton?', 17),
(11087, '27', 'Robb will have sent a force to retake Winterfell by now.', 17),
(11088, '270', 'Does he need to lie down?', 17),
(11089, '271', 'Have the men build him a new pen.', 17),
(11090, '272', 'Put him in with the Kingslayer for now.', 17),
(11091, '273', 'Have your boy watch over them.', 17),
(11092, '274', 'Torrhen.', 17),
(11093, '275', 'That will be all.', 17),
(11094, '276', 'Your Grace.', 17),
(11095, '277', 'A minute of your time?', 17),
(11096, '278', 'I\'ve been treating your wounded men.', 17),
(11097, '279', 'And my enemies, as some of my bannermen are fond of mentioning.', 17),
(11098, '28', 'Robb\'s in the Riverlands. My sister\'s in Deepwood Motte.', 17),
(11099, '280', 'They\'re not my enemies.', 17),
(11100, '281', 'That\'s what I tell my bannermen.', 17),
(11101, '282', 'I\'ve already run through the supplies I brought with me.', 17),
(11102, '283', 'Some are easily replaced. Egg yolks, turpentine, oil of roses.', 17),
(11103, '284', 'But some are not.', 17),
(11104, '285', 'I need silk for stitching.', 17),
(11105, '286', 'I need fennel root for those with fever, willow bark. Mostly I need milk of the poppy.', 17),
(11106, '287', 'You saw what it was like to amputate a foot without any.', 17),
(11107, '288', 'I assume there will be more loss of limb before this war is over.', 17),
(11108, '289', '- If you need help finding these... - I know where to find them.', 17),
(11109, '29', 'She\'ll get here long before they do.', 17),
(11110, '290', 'I\'m sorry, I shouldn\'t interrupt you.', 17),
(11111, '291', 'Continue, my lady.', 17),
(11112, '292', 'You\'re riding to the Crag to negotiate a surrender?', 17),
(11113, '293', 'Yes.', 17),
(11114, '294', 'The Crag will have a maester and he will have what I need.', 17),
(11115, '295', 'I expect he will.', 17),
(11116, '296', 'If I could write a list.', 17),
(11117, '297', 'Come with me to the Crag.', 17),
(11118, '298', 'I don\'t think that will be...', 17),
(11119, '299', 'Let the maester show you his stores.', 17),
(11120, '3', 'The boy can\'t walk, but somehow he slipped past you?', 17),
(11121, '30', 'And Ned Stark always said 500 men could hold Winterfell against 10,000.', 17),
(11122, '300', 'I want the wounded men to be treated well,', 17),
(11123, '301', 'all the wounded men.', 17),
(11124, '302', '- Children, come inside, quick. - Come on.', 17),
(11125, '303', 'Hurry up!', 17),
(11126, '304', 'Can\'t find anything, ser.', 17),
(11127, '305', '- They\'ve lost the scent. - Try again.', 17),
(11128, '306', 'We\'ve circled this farmhouse twice. There\'s no sign of them.', 17),
(11129, '307', 'We could start the search fresh in the morning, my lord.', 17),
(11130, '308', 'I\'m looking at spending the rest of my life', 17),
(11131, '309', 'being treated like a fool and a eunuch by my own people.', 17),
(11132, '31', 'We have a scent!', 17),
(11133, '310', 'Ask yourself, is there anything I wouldn\'t do to stop that from happening?', 17),
(11134, '311', 'The hounds will find the scent again. I\'ll beat them until they do.', 17),
(11135, '312', 'I\'ll whip every man here until I have both those boys in hand.', 17),
(11136, '313', 'And once I\'ve got them, the pampered little shits...', 17),
(11137, '314', 'It\'s better to be cruel than weak.', 17),
(11138, '315', 'Prince Theon.', 17),
(11139, '316', '- Where are they? - Who, m\'lord?', 17),
(11140, '317', 'The Stark boys. Where are they?', 17),
(11141, '318', 'I don\'t know. I seen no one.', 17),
(11142, '319', 'Think harder.', 17),
(11143, '32', 'The hounds have the scent.', 17),
(11144, '320', 'I swear, m\'lord. I don\'t know.', 17),
(11145, '321', 'My lord, over here.', 17),
(11146, '322', 'I think I\'ve found what we\'re looking for.', 17),
(11147, '323', 'Send the old man home.', 17),
(11148, '324', 'Go back to Winterfell.', 17),
(11149, '325', 'Take him back.', 17),
(11150, '326', 'Theon, don\'t do this.', 17),
(11151, '327', '- You came back. - As soon as I heard.', 17),
(11152, '328', 'Do you know anything?', 17),
(11153, '329', '- Irri is dead. - I know.', 17),
